external_knowledge:
Highly cited publications refer to those with the highest citation count for each author and journal; 
Open access publications are those with 'is_open_access' equal to 1;
The publication year range is between 2015 and 2020 (inclusive).

sql:
SELECT journal_name, impact_factor, category, COUNT(*) OVER () AS total_journals
FROM journals
WHERE category = 'biology';

SELECT journal_name, impact_factor, COUNT(*) OVER () AS total_journals, MAX(impact_factor) OVER () AS highest_impact_factor
FROM journals
WHERE journal_id = 0;
